                           <desc>Fol.154vb: Purchase note.  </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is crudely written. The rubricated names of the buyer priest (qäsis) Wäldä Mikaʾel and that of his son Zärʾa Yoḥannǝs are barely legible.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#155r">Fols. 155r-156</locus>v: Fragment of an older lectionary (containing, among others, readings from the Epistles).<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written on leaves originating from an older (15th-cent.?) codex. In the margin of fol. 155rb the word bä-Ṭǝmqät is written in red indicating the reading for the feast of Baptism.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- A few corrections are written over erasures: e.g., fols. 44rb, 55rab, 83ra, 98rab.&#xD;
